WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.872 --> 00:00:06.942
Previously on Prison Break:

2
00:00:07.125 --> 00:00:09.006
Hey. yo. we're headed out man.

3
00:00:09.653 --> 00:00:10.824
Good luck.

4
00:00:11.425 --> 00:00:12.940
I hope you find
the girl. buddy.

5
00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:14.347
Baby. what the
hell is going on?

6
00:00:14.377 --> 00:00:17.311
Yeah. well Hector says that you
can serve your full sentence.

7
00:00:17.341 --> 00:00:18.954
What are you doing here.
where's Maricruz?

8
00:00:18.984 --> 00:00:20.156
She's with me now.

9
00:00:20.295 --> 00:00:22.836
What's this I hear about
you coming home soon?

10
00:00:22.887 --> 00:00:25.012
You're not getting your
daughter's hopes up are you?

11
00:00:25.042 --> 00:00:28.579
You sitting down?
Your man is coming home this week.

12
00:00:28.667 --> 00:00:30.453
We can make it to the
courthouse on foot from here.

13
00:00:30.486 --> 00:00:33.073
You don't understand.
everything is in that car.

14
00:00:33.308 --> 00:00:36.311
I've been clean
for 18 months now.

15
00:00:36.366 --> 00:00:40.220
I want to help people get from
where I've been to where I am.

16
00:00:43.105 --> 00:00:46.251
You were right. I should never
have gotten you involved in this.

17
00:00:46.286 --> 00:00:50.332
I just need to know what
Michael Scofield wanted from you

18
00:00:50.385 --> 00:00:51.931
in exchange for the green card.

19
00:00:51.975 --> 00:00:54.013
Caroline. I've been
doing this for 15 years

20
00:00:54.045 --> 00:00:56.502
and it's never been about anything
other than you. your family

21
00:00:56.537 --> 00:00:58.460
and. most importantly.
this country.

22
00:00:58.555 --> 00:01:00.681
Now. I need to know who
I'm working for here.

23
00:01:00.718 --> 00:01:02.832
You are working for me.

24
00:01:02.925 --> 00:01:06.500
Are you aware of any arrangement
Officer Bellick had with any inmate

25
00:01:06.557 --> 00:01:08.053
regarding Prison Industries?

26
00:01:08.156 --> 00:01:10.392
Yeah. he sold it
to John Abruzzi.

27
00:01:10.487 --> 00:01:14.130
Officer Brad Bellick. you're terminated.
effective immediately.

28
00:01:14.237 --> 00:01:17.343
They just announced
the rewards on the TV.

29
00:01:17.437 --> 00:01:21.011
- How much?
- $100.000 a piece.

30
00:01:21.398 --> 00:01:25.723
The money is just
outside of Tooele. Utah.

31
00:01:28.955 --> 00:01:29.702
Truck!

32
00:01:35.815 --> 00:01:37.510
Get men in all the
area hospitals.

33
00:01:37.596 --> 00:01:39.481
Wherever they are.
one of them is bleeding good.

34
00:01:39.517 --> 00:01:41.963
- We got to move.
- I can't.

35
00:01:47.616 --> 00:01:50.013
You put in all that work.
break out of prison.

36
00:01:50.105 --> 00:01:52.501
only to end up dead at
the bottom of a ditch.

37
00:01:52.788 --> 00:01:56.741
Kind of sad really.
So which one of them was it?

38
00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:04.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

39
00:02:08.545 --> 00:02:10.432
We've got a blanket
on all the hospitals.

40
00:02:10.468 --> 00:02:11.492
Free clinics?

41
00:02:11.585 --> 00:02:14.713
If they've got Band-Aids and Bactine.
we've got a body in there.

42
00:02:14.747 --> 00:02:16.211
The brothers come
in for medical.

43
00:02:16.247 --> 00:02:18.323
they're getting it in a van
on the way back to Fox River.

44
00:02:18.358 --> 00:02:20.143
Anything break on
the other six?

45
00:02:20.417 --> 00:02:23.241
Eyes and ears on the families.
So far. no hits.

46
00:02:23.425 --> 00:02:24.583
Maybe just laying low.

47
00:02:24.675 --> 00:02:27.372
What's the hardest thing in
the world for a con to do?

48
00:02:27.396 --> 00:02:28.232
Nothing?

49
00:02:28.336 --> 00:02:30.083
Few things in life
are certain. Ms...?

50
00:02:30.117 --> 00:02:30.573
Lang.

51
00:02:30.807 --> 00:02:33.542
Death. taxes and the fact
that a man on the run

52
00:02:33.588 --> 00:02:36.131
will make a mistake sometime
in the first 72 hours.

53
00:02:36.218 --> 00:02:37.401
Needing distance.
he'll steal a car.

54
00:02:37.438 --> 00:02:38.992
Needing money.
he'll rob a store.

55
00:02:39.027 --> 00:02:42.182
Needing help.
he'll trust someone that he shouldn't.

56
00:02:42.327 --> 00:02:43.823
And when he does...

57
00:02:44.058 --> 00:02:47.201
he will leave behind the crumbs
that will take us right to him.

58
00:02:53.395 --> 00:02:54.942
I need your help.

59
00:02:55.037 --> 00:02:57.350
- Michael. what are you doing?
- Cayenne pepper.

60
00:02:57.386 --> 00:02:58.120
What?

61
00:02:58.456 --> 00:03:03.973
- In your kitchen. do you have any?
- Um... yeah. maybe.

62
00:03:04.296 --> 00:03:06.092
I'm gonna need some
rubbing alcohol.

63
00:03:06.358 --> 00:03:09.171
some towels and pain killers.
whatever you got.

64
00:03:09.316 --> 00:03:11.103
- Some booze.
- Please!

65
00:03:17.717 --> 00:03:20.973
Easy. easy. easy. easy.

66
00:03:25.328 --> 00:03:27.433
It's fine. man.
let's just keep moving.

67
00:03:27.526 --> 00:03:30.962
We keep moving and that
leg keeps bleeding.

68
00:03:31.058 --> 00:03:34.170
The leg keeps bleeding and we're
not getting out of Illinois.

69
00:03:34.265 --> 00:03:35.952
This is going to hurt.

70
00:03:37.247 --> 00:03:40.163
That's good. that's good.
that's good.

71
00:03:42.118 --> 00:03:46.492
- This will seal the capillaries.
- Michael. you should not have come here.

72
00:03:46.545 --> 00:03:49.472
- The police have been here asking questions.
- We didn't have a choice.

73
00:03:49.508 --> 00:03:52.013
Listen. you know I'm thankful
for the help with the green card.

74
00:03:52.048 --> 00:03:53.461
but I just don't want
to get involved.

75
00:03:53.498 --> 00:03:56.291
I know. I know it wasn't part
of our deal. I know. Inow.

76
00:03:56.316 --> 00:04:01.362
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
But there was nowhere else to go.

77
00:04:01.458 --> 00:04:03.903
When I saw you on the news.
I was worried.

78
00:04:04.135 --> 00:04:07.012
I just hoped you crossed
the border by now.

79
00:04:07.108 --> 00:04:08.793
So did I.

80
00:04:11.616 --> 00:04:13.350
Keep giving him these.

81
00:04:13.638 --> 00:04:15.791
See if you can find
him some clean clothes.

82
00:04:15.886 --> 00:04:16.580
O kay.

83
00:04:17.235 --> 00:04:18.972
I got to go back
and get our car.

84
00:04:19.385 --> 00:04:22.593
Forget the car.
We can get another.

85
00:04:22.687 --> 00:04:24.750
I don't need a car.
I need that car.

86
00:04:24.846 --> 00:04:25.772
Why?

87
00:04:27.798 --> 00:04:33.070
Because in that car is
everything we need to disappear.

88
00:05:14.118 --> 00:05:15.962
- What have you got?
- Here we go boss.

89
00:05:15.998 --> 00:05:18.732
one of the blues hauled in a
vagrant a couple hours ago.

90
00:05:18.767 --> 00:05:20.852
Seems the man was in
possession of an item or two

91
00:05:20.887 --> 00:05:22.943
that didn't exactly
belong to him.

92
00:05:34.146 --> 00:05:36.313
Looks like we got
our first mistake.

93
00:06:00.648 --> 00:06:04.109
<i>~ Season 2 - Episode 3 ~
"Scan"</i>

94
00:06:19.858 --> 00:06:22.300
Hey. you got any of
that oriental jerky?

95
00:06:22.395 --> 00:06:23.473
Excuse me?

96
00:06:24.215 --> 00:06:26.281
Teriyaki flavor.

97
00:06:27.187 --> 00:06:28.023
No.

98
00:06:28.865 --> 00:06:30.782
You got any in the back?

99
00:06:31.666 --> 00:06:33.922
Uh. let me check.

100
00:06:34.018 --> 00:06:37.180
And. give me a bottle of that Early
Times while you're back there. junior.

101
00:06:37.215 --> 00:06:39.010
Feel free to earn
your paycheck today.

102
00:06:39.045 --> 00:06:41.212
Watch the store.
I'll be right back.

103
00:06:47.228 --> 00:06:48.732
How goes it. Roy?

104
00:06:59.608 --> 00:07:02.681
To be honest. Roy. I could've done
without the knee to the junk.

105
00:07:02.717 --> 00:07:06.240
You bit me. Brad.
Like a little girl. you bite me.

106
00:07:06.386 --> 00:07:09.111
- Well. you had it coming.
- Yeah. probably did.

107
00:07:10.878 --> 00:07:11.891
You know it's crazy.

108
00:07:12.038 --> 00:07:14.631
us taking it out on each other
for how things turned out.

109
00:07:14.668 --> 00:07:15.801
You want someone to blame.

110
00:07:15.837 --> 00:07:19.742
how about those convicts staring up
at us from the papers every morning.

111
00:07:20.075 --> 00:07:25.822
They took my job.
my pension. my dignity.

112
00:07:25.878 --> 00:07:29.091
When they went over that wall. they
took all of it right along with them.

113
00:07:29.127 --> 00:07:32.270
Everything I worked
for my whole life.

114
00:07:32.376 --> 00:07:34.673
See that reward they got?

115
00:07:34.765 --> 00:07:38.063
Those ass-hats are worth more
dead than you and I are alive.

116
00:07:38.158 --> 00:07:40.740
- Not for long.
- What do you mean?

117
00:07:40.838 --> 00:07:44.983
I mean somebody's going to get
that money. might as well be me.

118
00:07:47.028 --> 00:07:48.903
You know a job like that might

119
00:07:48.996 --> 00:07:51.443
go a little smoother with
an extra pair of hands.

120
00:07:51.536 --> 00:07:53.853
You really think I'm going to
split that reward with you?

121
00:07:53.888 --> 00:07:57.383
I'm just saying. you run into those
brothers. two of them. one of you.

122
00:07:57.545 --> 00:08:00.093
You might find yourself
wishing for a good wingman.

123
00:08:15.127 --> 00:08:16.962
Just get it done. Mike.

124
00:08:19.085 --> 00:08:21.390
- How are you doing?
- May I help you?

125
00:08:21.448 --> 00:08:23.600
Yeah. I hope so. Chuck.

126
00:08:24.485 --> 00:08:26.591
I think you may
have towed my car.

127
00:08:27.718 --> 00:08:30.112
- What did it look like?
- What did it look like?

128
00:08:30.246 --> 00:08:33.641
The car you stole the backpack from.
What did it look like?

129
00:08:34.005 --> 00:08:38.442
- I don't know. man. maybe it was gray.
- It's a gray Accord.

130
00:08:39.085 --> 00:08:40.402
License number?

131
00:08:40.495 --> 00:08:43.360
Look. man. that's all I know.
I wasn't after the car.

132
00:08:43.785 --> 00:08:46.410
Thought the bag had
some clothes in it.

133
00:08:46.507 --> 00:08:48.263
You remember where
the car was parked?

134
00:08:48.296 --> 00:08:51.870
- Where'd you park it?
- Corner of Hancock and 15th.

135
00:08:51.965 --> 00:08:54.640
I don't know.
maybe around 15th somewhere.

136
00:08:54.975 --> 00:08:57.040
but it ain't going
to be there anymore.

137
00:08:57.065 --> 00:08:58.182
What do you mean?

138
00:08:58.238 --> 00:09:01.011
That's the reason I didn't
get to grab anything else.

139
00:09:01.105 --> 00:09:04.003
- Tow truck rolls up.
- Already on it.

140
00:09:04.745 --> 00:09:09.082
Okay. It's going to be
60 bucks for the tow.

141
00:09:09.407 --> 00:09:11.332
and 24 for the overnight.

142
00:09:24.597 --> 00:09:27.223
All right.
be right back with your vehicle.

143
00:09:27.326 --> 00:09:29.061
Shouldn't take
but a few minutes.

144
00:09:38.915 --> 00:09:41.032
- Hello?
- Petey. it's Sucre.

145
00:09:41.265 --> 00:09:44.751
- As in. Fernando Sucre?
- Is there another one?

146
00:09:44.842 --> 00:09:48.789
Man. I hope not. But my boy Sucre would
not be calling me on the telephone.

147
00:09:48.877 --> 00:09:52.833
thereby making me an accessory
to his dumb-ass escape. man.

148
00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.983
I'm sorry. bro. I just...
I just...

149
00:09:55.076 --> 00:09:57.051
I just need you to get
a hold of Maricruz.

150
00:09:57.086 --> 00:09:59.922
I can't call her cell because the
Feds will be all over the place...

151
00:09:59.958 --> 00:10:03.011
Homie. listen. man.
you have got to forget about that girl.

152
00:10:03.158 --> 00:10:05.000
If I could forget
about her. pendejo.

153
00:10:05.035 --> 00:10:08.192
I'd still be at Fox River.
sitting in cell 40 on your old bunk.

154
00:10:08.287 --> 00:10:10.552
Yeah. well. I hope you're
holding on to something tight

155
00:10:10.588 --> 00:10:12.571
'cause I'm about to break
it down for you. brother.

156
00:10:12.605 --> 00:10:15.763
She's getting married
to Hector on Saturday.

157
00:10:16.228 --> 00:10:20.933
- What day is today?
- Thursday. bro. Sorry. man.

158
00:10:24.088 --> 00:10:28.421
All right. you got to get
her to your place tonight.

159
00:10:28.515 --> 00:10:31.711
I got one last shot to make
her change her mind. dude.

160
00:10:32.277 --> 00:10:34.223
Just find a way to
get her there. okay?

161
00:10:35.026 --> 00:10:36.863
Wait... Sucre. hang on. man.

162
00:11:10.367 --> 00:11:13.661
About the. uh...
about the broken window.

163
00:11:13.758 --> 00:11:15.603
Yeah. we got a disclaimer
posted right there on the wall.

164
00:11:15.637 --> 00:11:16.911
says we're not responsible...

165
00:11:16.946 --> 00:11:20.002
Yeah. I don't... I don't care
about the broken window. Chuck.

166
00:11:21.995 --> 00:11:26.090
- I had a backpack inside.
- Not when we got it.

167
00:11:26.465 --> 00:11:28.721
I got some paperwork
for you to fill out.

168
00:11:33.836 --> 00:11:35.662
You look familiar.

169
00:11:38.817 --> 00:11:43.761
Yeah. you... you were the attending
when I first started here.

170
00:11:43.867 --> 00:11:44.840
Sure.

171
00:11:45.815 --> 00:11:49.721
Um. would one of you mind
calling me a cab. please?

172
00:11:50.236 --> 00:11:52.060
I don't think so.

173
00:11:53.567 --> 00:11:55.443
Look. Dr. Tancredi. I...

174
00:11:56.505 --> 00:11:57.952
I just want to say good luck.

175
00:11:58.057 --> 00:11:59.742
- Sara Tancredi?
- I'm sorry.

176
00:11:59.845 --> 00:12:01.303
You have the right
to remain silent.

177
00:12:01.336 --> 00:12:03.382
Please place your
hands behind your back.

178
00:12:03.676 --> 00:12:05.990
If you have any questions.
I'm happy to come down to...

179
00:12:06.027 --> 00:12:07.970
Ms. Tancredi.
out of respect for your father.

180
00:12:08.006 --> 00:12:10.442
- I'm going to ask you again.
- My father?

181
00:12:10.548 --> 00:12:14.212
I'm sure he'd prefer that
this went without incident.

182
00:12:14.296 --> 00:12:17.531
You have the right to speak to an
attorney before you speak to the police.

183
00:12:17.567 --> 00:12:21.143
Anything you say may be used
against you in a court of law.

184
00:12:21.235 --> 00:12:24.833
And to have an attorney present during
questioning now or in the future.

185
00:12:26.068 --> 00:12:27.663
Caroline. they're
taking her in.

186
00:12:29.688 --> 00:12:32.270
Of course.
I'll keep an eye on her.

187
00:12:34.535 --> 00:12:37.831
All you got to do is sign
here at the bottom...

188
00:12:38.016 --> 00:12:39.610
and be on your way.

189
00:12:39.987 --> 00:12:41.531
Excuse me. please.

190
00:12:43.438 --> 00:12:44.690
Brewster's Towing.

191
00:12:44.837 --> 00:12:48.792
This is Agent Mahone with the FBI.
Who am I speaking with?

192
00:12:49.306 --> 00:12:50.041
Chuck.

193
00:12:50.237 --> 00:12:52.781
Okay. Chuck. I want to alert
you to a possible situation.

194
00:12:52.818 --> 00:12:54.232
Are you listening to me. Chuck?

195
00:12:54.268 --> 00:12:56.541
An individual may be coming
there to inquire about a vehicle.

196
00:12:56.575 --> 00:12:59.723
A gray Accord.
probably with a busted rear window.

197
00:12:59.868 --> 00:13:03.412
Has anyone come by looking for a
vehicle that matches that description?

198
00:13:08.665 --> 00:13:10.071
Yes. sir.

199
00:13:10.407 --> 00:13:11.381
When?

200
00:13:12.266 --> 00:13:14.891
Uh...

201
00:13:15.736 --> 00:13:16.570
Chuck.

202
00:13:16.705 --> 00:13:18.721
Will you tell me
when he was there?

203
00:13:20.026 --> 00:13:22.232
Right now.

204
00:13:28.235 --> 00:13:32.091
Scofield's there.
Chuck. stall him.

205
00:13:32.186 --> 00:13:34.360
We've got people on the way-
do not let him leave.

206
00:13:34.397 --> 00:13:37.462
- Do not let him leave.
- It's my supervisor. he...

207
00:13:37.675 --> 00:13:40.973
I just got to get clearance
before I can release the car.

208
00:13:42.245 --> 00:13:44.503
Chuck. you there? Hey. Chuck.

209
00:13:44.597 --> 00:13:47.091
Okay. come on. come on.
Chuck. you still with me?

210
00:13:48.488 --> 00:13:52.670
Yeah. that vehicle might not
be here when you get here.

211
00:13:53.185 --> 00:13:57.000
- You need to send somebody now.
- Do not let him leave!

212
00:13:59.787 --> 00:14:01.232
Oh. he got the keys.

213
00:14:05.775 --> 00:14:09.491
- Where the hell are those units?!
- Still six or seven minutes out. sir.

214
00:14:15.356 --> 00:14:18.741
We got chatter; it's Franklin.
He's at a payphone Downtown.

215
00:14:18.886 --> 00:14:20.193
Mistake number two.

216
00:14:22.518 --> 00:14:25.950
Look. I know. I know. baby.
just let me explain. all right?

217
00:14:26.048 --> 00:14:28.010
Were you ever even
in the military?

218
00:14:28.345 --> 00:14:32.443
I served my country.
and my country served me up. All right?

219
00:14:32.536 --> 00:14:36.072
Look. I wish I could lay this all
out for you right here. right now.

220
00:14:36.908 --> 00:14:39.910
But just know. baby.
I am sorry. and I love you.

221
00:14:40.246 --> 00:14:42.790
and when the time comes.
I will explain everything.

222
00:14:44.168 --> 00:14:48.172
Give me one good reason why I
shouldn't turn you in right now.

223
00:14:48.318 --> 00:14:50.242
You know what?
I'll give you three.

224
00:14:50.387 --> 00:14:55.050
Me. you.
and that beautiful little girl of ours.

225
00:14:55.746 --> 00:14:59.943
I got a plan. I got a plan that
is going to get us some money.

226
00:15:00.075 --> 00:15:03.003
where you and I and our baby-

227
00:15:03.137 --> 00:15:06.012
nobody can ever find
us or bother us again.

228
00:15:06.107 --> 00:15:07.303
You got to trust me.

229
00:15:07.396 --> 00:15:11.451
That's all I need is the opportunity
for you to hear me out. All right?

230
00:15:14.366 --> 00:15:15.340
All right.

231
00:15:16.966 --> 00:15:23.151
All right. listen. Has anybody
tried to contact you about me?

232
00:15:23.886 --> 00:15:25.911
- No.
- Okay.

233
00:15:26.058 --> 00:15:28.262
Okay. that's good. that's good.

234
00:15:29.047 --> 00:15:31.212
Listen.

235
00:15:31.767 --> 00:15:36.712
In the Rainbow Room...
Restaurant. New York City.

236
00:15:36.816 --> 00:15:41.811
Do you remember that beautiful
spot where we took that picture?

237
00:15:43.066 --> 00:15:45.171
The one by the window?

238
00:15:47.077 --> 00:15:48.433
Mm-hmm.

239
00:15:51.026 --> 00:15:56.491
I am going a be waiting in
that spot one week from now.

240
00:15:57.376 --> 00:16:00.533
And that's all that I
want in this whole world

241
00:16:00.627 --> 00:16:02.751
is for my two girls to
be waiting there for me.

242
00:16:02.786 --> 00:16:04.711
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

243
00:16:04.808 --> 00:16:06.592
Look. I got to go.

244
00:16:06.866 --> 00:16:10.962
Baby. I just want to know.
are you going to be there?

245
00:16:11.065 --> 00:16:12.940
I don't know.

246
00:16:13.866 --> 00:16:15.553
But you know me.

247
00:16:15.728 --> 00:16:17.601
- Do I?
- Yes!

248
00:16:18.437 --> 00:16:20.740
Good-bye. Miles.

249
00:16:28.007 --> 00:16:29.800
I'll alert the field
office in Manhattan.

250
00:16:29.836 --> 00:16:32.391
have them send Franklin's picture to
every employee at the Rainbow Room.

251
00:16:32.427 --> 00:16:34.792
Then go have a chat with
his wife. woman-to-woman.

252
00:16:34.827 --> 00:16:37.750
Ask her why she never once
visited her husband at Fox River.

253
00:16:37.785 --> 00:16:40.051
Pretend you don't know the answer.
That relationship is fragile.

254
00:16:40.085 --> 00:16:42.571
We keep tapping on cracks.
and she's going to break.

255
00:16:42.605 --> 00:16:44.712
Yes. sir.
I appreciate the assignment. I...

256
00:16:44.747 --> 00:16:48.371
Lang. I don't need gratitude.
I need leads. answers. progress.

257
00:16:48.515 --> 00:16:51.291
Anybody that can't deliver
that just don't even unpack.

258
00:16:51.385 --> 00:16:53.170
- Clear?
- Yes. sir.

259
00:16:55.718 --> 00:16:58.820
- Mr. Wheeler.
- Stand by.

260
00:16:58.925 --> 00:17:01.473
Stay on Scofield. I want the
license plate number on that Accord

261
00:17:01.505 --> 00:17:03.760
and I want you to get
it out on the wire.

262
00:17:03.955 --> 00:17:06.491
- Yeah.
- Now.

263
00:17:06.637 --> 00:17:07.852
I'll call you back.

264
00:17:13.916 --> 00:17:15.501
What's going on?

265
00:17:17.828 --> 00:17:20.330
Apparently. I wasn't the only
one looking for this car.

266
00:17:20.376 --> 00:17:23.130
Great! Let's get out of here.

267
00:17:29.208 --> 00:17:31.360
I'm sorry I had to
involve you in this.

268
00:17:31.926 --> 00:17:35.550
I mean.
any more than I already have.

269
00:17:38.517 --> 00:17:39.821
Good luck.

270
00:17:41.588 --> 00:17:43.132
To you. too.

271
00:17:44.896 --> 00:17:46.581
So. um...

272
00:17:51.715 --> 00:17:53.033
I'll see you.

273
00:17:54.286 --> 00:17:56.010
Yeah. I hope so.

274
00:18:09.398 --> 00:18:10.610
You all right?

275
00:18:11.216 --> 00:18:13.940
- Yeah.
- Good.

276
00:18:14.917 --> 00:18:18.363
We're heading west.
toward the money. toward LJ.

277
00:18:18.458 --> 00:18:20.422
We just got one
more stop to make.

278
00:18:20.775 --> 00:18:22.131
What for?

279
00:18:24.246 --> 00:18:25.752
You trust me?

280
00:18:25.885 --> 00:18:27.531
Of course I trust you. Brad.

281
00:18:27.677 --> 00:18:30.973
It's just that if anybody
finds out about this. I...

282
00:18:31.065 --> 00:18:32.092
They won't.

283
00:18:36.625 --> 00:18:38.440
Let me handle this.

284
00:18:43.575 --> 00:18:46.353
Humpty Dumpty
climbed up a wall.

285
00:18:46.818 --> 00:18:50.162
Humpty Dumpty had a great fall.

286
00:18:51.556 --> 00:18:54.890
Look... I already told the feds
I don't know anything. okay?

287
00:18:55.037 --> 00:18:58.523
Those suits with pedicures and
penny loafers. Why would you?

288
00:18:58.618 --> 00:19:00.972
They have rules to follow.
codes of conduct.

289
00:19:01.067 --> 00:19:04.692
They got jobs to protect.
Now me. on the other hand.

290
00:19:04.785 --> 00:19:06.901
Come on. Boss. I swear.

291
00:19:06.997 --> 00:19:09.291
Those guys didn't let
me in on any plans.

292
00:19:09.396 --> 00:19:13.581
Then you're telling me in all
your little powwows in the yard.

293
00:19:13.916 --> 00:19:16.232
they never once mentioned
what they were going to do

294
00:19:16.265 --> 00:19:19.411
- once they went over that wall?
- That's right.

295
00:19:24.886 --> 00:19:29.503
Now... I may not work
here anymore. Big-uns.

296
00:19:29.648 --> 00:19:31.670
but I still got influence
with people who do.

297
00:19:31.706 --> 00:19:38.362
people who will do whatever I ask
them to to whoever I ask them to.

298
00:19:40.905 --> 00:19:45.812
And a...
curvy man like yourself.

299
00:19:45.907 --> 00:19:49.061
well. let's just say there's
some filthy individuals

300
00:19:49.157 --> 00:19:53.871
who might enjoy a cellie
with womanly attributes.

301
00:19:57.015 --> 00:20:00.591
Now. you're going to tell
me everything you know

302
00:20:00.927 --> 00:20:03.891
about where those
convicts are headed.

303
00:20:04.585 --> 00:20:09.063
or I'm going to throw your
fat ass to the wolves.

304
00:20:13.647 --> 00:20:15.283
Okay. thanks.

305
00:20:15.517 --> 00:20:18.060
Mistake number three:
someone reported seeing a man

306
00:20:18.158 --> 00:20:21.491
