obtain a key to the infirmary.

331
00:21:51.677 --> 00:21:53.262
I can't do that.

332
00:21:53.356 --> 00:21:56.651
Oh. yes you can. Sara.
You can do that and you will.

333
00:21:57.116 --> 00:21:59.892
I did it. Dad.

334
00:22:01.608 --> 00:22:04.722
I left the door open.
me and no one else.

335
00:22:05.415 --> 00:22:07.052
That's not true.

336
00:22:07.387 --> 00:22:10.060
- Yes. it is.
- That's not true.

337
00:22:12.197 --> 00:22:17.571
Sara... just do
what you're told.

338
00:22:17.946 --> 00:22:21.752
otherwise there will
be consequences...

339
00:22:22.176 --> 00:22:24.573
that will affect us all.

340
00:22:24.716 --> 00:22:27.631
Do you understand
what I'm telling you?

341
00:22:27.956 --> 00:22:29.262
Yes. sir.

342
00:22:30.107 --> 00:22:31.273
Good.

343
00:22:34.415 --> 00:22:36.061
In one week...

344
00:22:36.295 --> 00:22:39.323
I will be appointed the new Vice
President of the United States.

345
00:22:39.357 --> 00:22:41.941
There will be a ceremony.
you will be invited.

346
00:22:42.408 --> 00:22:44.892
but you will not attend.

347
00:22:47.306 --> 00:22:49.041
Good-bye. Sara.

348
00:23:04.478 --> 00:23:06.301
- Let's put some music on.
- Don't.

349
00:23:07.187 --> 00:23:10.290
I forgot. No radio.

350
00:23:11.037 --> 00:23:15.423
Man. it's quiet out here. Inside.
there was always noise. you know?

351
00:23:15.516 --> 00:23:19.282
Someone yelling. guards making rounds.
I got used to it.

352
00:23:19.376 --> 00:23:22.240
You're right.
We should go back.

353
00:23:26.786 --> 00:23:30.412
The tats... they weren't just
for getting out. were they?

354
00:23:31.067 --> 00:23:33.791
Breaking out was
just the beginning.

355
00:23:33.887 --> 00:23:35.443
Now. it gets a little
more interesting.

356
00:23:35.475 --> 00:23:39.073
Mm-hmm. 'cause me being strapped to the
electric chair wasn't interesting enough.

357
00:23:39.108 --> 00:23:42.452
All I'm saying is inside.
we had the element of surprise.

358
00:23:42.545 --> 00:23:44.803
No one knew what
we were planning.

359
00:23:46.057 --> 00:23:49.821
There's something about this guy-
the one in the elevator.

360
00:23:51.206 --> 00:23:52.420
It's like...

361
00:23:53.676 --> 00:23:55.332
it's like he knows
where we're going.

362
00:23:55.368 --> 00:23:57.572
what we're thinking.
If that's true.

363
00:23:57.718 --> 00:24:00.743
it's just a matter of time before he
finds out about the money in Utah.

364
00:24:00.775 --> 00:24:03.173
Bolshoi Booze.
our way into Mexico.

365
00:24:03.588 --> 00:24:05.940
E verything.

366
00:24:13.808 --> 00:24:17.761
- Are you ready for this?
- Make the call.

367
00:24:23.027 --> 00:24:24.760
Please leave a message.

368
00:24:25.176 --> 00:24:30.600
Hey. it's me. I've got Linc.

369
00:24:31.206 --> 00:24:33.130
We're on our way there.

370
00:24:33.225 --> 00:24:38.693
If for some reason you can't make it.
call me back at 9-1-7-4-5...

371
00:24:39.066 --> 00:24:40.810
We just got this
from surveillance.

372
00:24:40.898 --> 00:24:44.091
You remember that voicemail Scofield
prepaid for when he went off to prison?

373
00:24:44.128 --> 00:24:44.730
Yeah.

374
00:24:44.917 --> 00:24:47.083
Someone just left
a message on it.

375
00:24:47.177 --> 00:24:49.501
- Who?
- Scofield.

376
00:24:49.596 --> 00:24:51.992
Something... something
about a meeting.

377
00:24:52.096 --> 00:24:53.892
it sounded like he was
waiting for someone else

378
00:24:53.926 --> 00:24:55.722
to check the message
and then call him back.

379
00:24:55.757 --> 00:24:57.553
This prefix.
that's a cell phone number.

380
00:24:57.587 --> 00:24:58.620
As long as it's turned on...

381
00:24:58.655 --> 00:25:01.052
We can track
exactly where he is.

382
00:25:23.276 --> 00:25:24.860
Don't do anything stupid.

383
00:25:25.007 --> 00:25:27.062
Don't do anything stupid.

384
00:25:53.647 --> 00:25:55.993
Is there a problem. officer?

385
00:25:56.226 --> 00:25:58.761
You know why I pulled
you over today. sir?

386
00:25:59.097 --> 00:26:00.493
Speeding?

387
00:26:01.057 --> 00:26:03.541
Let me see your license
and registration please?

388
00:26:03.827 --> 00:26:07.781
The thing is. I. uh...
I lost my wallet.

389
00:26:08.246 --> 00:26:11.783
Well. I guess your registration
will have to do just fine then.

390
00:26:21.827 --> 00:26:27.671
So... this is your car.
Mrs. Miller?

391
00:26:28.137 --> 00:26:33.511
Mrs. Miller's my wife.
I'm Mr. Miller.

392
00:26:34.167 --> 00:26:40.152
Well... your tags are expired.
I'll be right back.

393
00:27:05.606 --> 00:27:07.010
Did he sing?

394
00:27:08.456 --> 00:27:11.042
Like a fat. sweaty bird.

395
00:27:24.877 --> 00:27:26.422
Hey. sweet pea.

396
00:27:26.567 --> 00:27:28.253
- Daddy?
- Hey. come here.

397
00:27:29.456 --> 00:27:31.951
Oh. look at you. You're so big.

398
00:27:33.296 --> 00:27:36.922
Hey. why don't you do me a
favor and grab a piece of chalk

399
00:27:37.066 --> 00:27:39.843
